@vladmoroz Since you didn't put a class on `Toggle` (only inside the render fn), I think it should be a simple fix of not including `className: undefined` in the render props.

But if you were to put classes in both places, we wouldn't be able to merge the classes, do you think it matters 🤔 

```jsx
// i know this is kind of a contrived example
<Toggle
  className={styles.Toggle}
  render={(props, state) => {
    if (state.pressed) {
      return (
        <button type="button" className={styles.pressed} {...props}>
          heart filled
        </button>
      );
    }

    return (
      <button type="button" className={styles.unpressed} {...props}>
        heart outline
      </button>
    );
  }}
/>
```
